Look at Figure 6.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Let's say we are endowed with outcomes given by AB.
 Self-insurance(CD) lowers the probability of low and high outcomes, thereby
 unambigously reducing the dispersion of outcomes.
 Self-protection, shift the distribution to the left, say EF, reduces the
 probability of low outcomes and raises the probability of high one and
 does not have an unambigous effect on the dispersion.
\end_layout

